edu.rit.pj2.tracker

Class TaskInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.rit.pj2.tracker.TaskInfo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Streamable

    public class TaskInfo
extends Object
implements Streamable
    Class TaskInfo is a record of information about a Task in a Job. It carries the information a Backend process needs to execute a Task as part of a Job.

    Task info objects are streamable. When a task info object is serialized and later deserialized, the input tuples are stored in serialized form in a private field, and the public inputTuples field is set to null. To get the input tuples back, call the unmarshalInputTuples() method. This is done to avoid deserializing the input tuples if the recipient does not need to use them or does not have the class files needed to deserialize them.
